"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035079","Treasury","false","2019-01-09","<p>HMRC regularly monitors its performance against its Compliance Yield target, which includes making assessments of the potential impacts of the redeployment of caseworkers. HMRC is on track to deliver the £30bn compliance yield target for 2018-19.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2019-01-09T15:43:28.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035079/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035079/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035079/answer",,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-01-04","Revenue and Customs: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to the HMRC Single Departmental Plan, published on 12 July 2018, what assessment HMRC has made of the effect on compliance yield of the redeployment of HMRC Compliance Caseworkers to undertake preparatory work on the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Chris Law","Dundee West","Chris Law","205291"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035080","Treasury","false","2019-01-09","<p>The Taxation (Cross-border Trade) Act 2018, which received Royal Assent on 13 September 2018, includes a series of substantive provisions and powers that will ensure functioning customs, VAT and excise regimes after EU exit.</p><p> </p><p>The government remains confident that all required SIs will be brought forward in good time.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2019-01-09T15:42:12.403Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035080/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035080/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035080/answer",,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-01-04","Revenue and Customs: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to the oral Evidence of the Permanent Secretary of HMRC of 5 November 2018 to the Public Accounts Committee, Question 152, what assessment he has made of the capacity of his Department to ensure that all legislation in relation to Customs, Vat and Excise required for the UK leaving the EU without a deal will be receive Royal Assent or Affirmative Resolution by 29 March 2019.","false","Biography information for Chris Law","Dundee West","Chris Law","205292"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035081","Treasury","false","2019-01-14","<p>The Working Time Regulations 1998 are explained to staff in HMRC HR Policy 28002. The policy details the responsibility of managers to monitor working hours to ensure compliance and action that they should take if their staff are working excessive hours.</p><p>HMRC discourages opting out of the working time regulations, with any opt outs restricted to a maximum period of 12 months. Opt outs are activity monitored both centrally and by the HR Business Partners embedded in the business.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2019-01-14T14:54:40.72Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035081/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035081/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035081/answer",,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-01-04","Revenue and Customs: Working Hours","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, what processes HMRC has in place to ensure compliance with Regulation 5 of the Working Time Regulations 1998 in relation to staff that work regularly in excess of 48 hours per week.","false","Biography information for Chris Law","Dundee West","Chris Law","205293"
